trans-unit.source: Completing synchronously means that the completer's future will be completed immediately when calling the complete or completeError method on a synchronous completer, which also calls any callbacks registered on that future.

trans-unit.source: Completing synchronously must not break the rule that when you add a callback on a future, that callback must not be called until the code that added the callback has completed. For that reason, a synchronous completion must only occur at the very end (in "tail position") of another synchronous event, because at that point, completing the future immediately is be equivalent to returning to the event loop and completing the future in the next microtask.

trans-unit.source: Conceptually, a MirrorsUsed annotation with override has the same effect as placing the annotation directly on the import of dart:mirrors in each of the referenced libraries. Thus, if the library had no MirrorsUsed annotation before, its unconditional import of dart:mirrors is overridden by an annotated import.
trans-unit.target: 概念的には、MirrorsUsedを持つ注釈オーバーライドは輸入に直接注釈を配置するのと同じ効果を持つ dart:mirrors 参照されるライブラリのそれぞれでを。したがって、ライブラリに以前にMirrorsUsedアノテーションがなかった場合、 dart:mirrors の無条件インポートは、アノテーション付きインポートによってオーバーライドされます。
